If you are ok with distinguishing the file/folder difference by the appearance of dots, you can apply the following XSLT-1.0 stylesheet:

- It uses a recursive template to get the string after the last `/`.
- Then it checks if this string contains a `.`

So, for a sample XML file like this:

    &lt;root&gt;
         &lt;img src=&#39;/.icons/rpm.gif&#39; alt=&#39;[DIR]&#39; width=&#39;16&#39; height=&#39;16&#39; /&gt;
         &lt;img src=&#39;/.icons/file.gif&#39; alt=&#39;[DIR]&#39; width=&#39;16&#39; height=&#39;16&#39; /&gt;
         &lt;img src=&#39;/.icons/someDir&#39; alt=&#39;[DIR]&#39; width=&#39;16&#39; height=&#39;16&#39; /&gt;
         &lt;img src=&#39;/.icons/folder.gif&#39; alt=&#39;[DIR]&#39; width=&#39;16&#39; height=&#39;16&#39; /&gt;
         &lt;img src=&#39;/.icons/anotherDir&#39; alt=&#39;[DIR]&#39; width=&#39;16&#39; height=&#39;16&#39; /&gt;
    &lt;/root&gt;

the XSLT 

    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
      &lt;xsl:output omit-xml-declaration=&quot;yes&quot; method=&quot;xml&quot; indent=&quot;yes&quot; /&gt; 
    
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;/root/img&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;filename&quot;&gt;
                &lt;xsl:call-template name=&quot;afterLastSlash&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:with-param name=&quot;str&quot; select=&quot;@src&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:call-template&gt;  
            &lt;/xsl:variable&gt;
            &lt;xsl:choose&gt;
                &lt;xsl:when test=&quot;contains($filename,&#39;.&#39;)&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;&#39;File&#39;&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:when&gt;
                &lt;xsl:otherwise&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;&#39;Directory&#39;&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:otherwise&gt;
            &lt;/xsl:choose&gt;       
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;  
    
        &lt;!-- get filename (string after last slash) --&gt;
        &lt;xsl:template name=&quot;afterLastSlash&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:param name=&quot;str&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;xsl:choose&gt;
                &lt;xsl:when test=&quot;substring-after($str,&#39;/&#39;) != &#39;&#39;&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:call-template name=&quot;afterLastSlash&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;xsl:with-param name=&quot;str&quot; select=&quot;substring-after($str,&#39;/&#39;)&quot; /&gt;
                    &lt;/xsl:call-template&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:when&gt;
                &lt;xsl:otherwise&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$str&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:otherwise&gt;
            &lt;/xsl:choose&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
        
    &lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;

yields the following result:

     File
     File
     Directory
     File
     Directory

---

With XSLT-2.0 or above the stylesheet can be reduced to

    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;/root/img&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:choose&gt;
            &lt;xsl:when test=&quot;contains(replace(@src,&#39;(.+/)?(.+)&#39;,&#39;$2&#39;),&#39;.&#39;)&quot;&gt;
