Don&#39;t take this wrong, but your code is so messed up in different places, that I&#39;d suggest you take another look at the absolute basics of JavaScript.

1. This is not valid JS syntax. It&#39;s basically an object that is never assigned to a variable.

```
{
    &quot;messages&quot;: [{
        &quot;msgFrom&quot;: &quot;13223821242&quot;,
        &quot;msgBody&quot;: &quot;Hi there&quot;
    }, {
        &quot;msgFrom&quot;: &quot;Bill&quot;,
        &quot;msgBody&quot;: &quot;Hello!&quot;
    }]
}
```

Remove the outer curly brackets and use `var messages = [...]` to set the array as a variable `messages`.

```
var messages = [{
    &quot;msgFrom&quot;: &quot;13223821242&quot;,
    &quot;msgBody&quot;: &quot;Hi there&quot;
}, {
    &quot;msgFrom&quot;: &quot;Bill&quot;,
    &quot;msgBody&quot;: &quot;Hello!&quot;
}]
```

2. You are never calling the anonymous arrow function that `loop` is a reference to. Call it via `loop()`.

3. this will result in an endless loop, as your return value is actually a function call, calling the referenced function again and again.

5. You return from your function before the `console.log()` is ever reached, so nothing will be logged.

6. You should push `messages[i]`, as `messages[1]` is always pushing the second element (JS indexes are zero-based)

To wrap it all up, here&#39;s the cleaned and running code (which is essentially doing nothing, as it just copies all elements from one array to another):

